    "methodology": "Caseload data from the DfE Children's Social Work Workforce census, collected annually from local authorities in England. Average caseload calculated as ratio of open cases to FTE social workers. Vacancy rate is unfilled posts as a percentage of total establishment. Turnover rate is leavers as a percentage of headcount. Agency worker proportion is agency FTE as a percentage of total FTE (employed plus agency). Children on child protection plans from DfE Characteristics of Children in Need return. Recommended maximum caseload of 12–15 from Community Care research and the Social Work Task Force (2009).",
